(95, 'Sandra Pérez Correa', 'Sandra Pérez Correa is Professor of Chemical Engineering and Biochemical Engineering at TECNM-Campus Veracruz, with focus on process design. She received her M. Sc. from the Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana at Iztapalapa in 2003 and B.S. from the Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México at Facultad de Química in Mexico, City. She has been a professor at TECNM since 2012.\n\nHer research interests include mathematical modelling of chemical processes, bioprocess design, process control, control structure design and optimal operation of process systems.', 'Education:\n• 2000: B.S. in Chemical Engineering at Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México (UNAM-Facultad de Química). Thesis: “Cinética de la cianuración de oro” (Thesis advisor: Gretchen T. Lapidus Lavine).\n\n• 2003: M.Sc. in Chemical Engineering at Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana - Iztapalapa. Thesis: “Estimación de estados de un reactor de polimerización de resinas alquidálicas” (Thesis advisor: Jesús Alvarez Calderón). Project supported (Award Grant) by the COMEX Polymer Research Center. University Merit Medal for M.Sc. studies.\n\nWork experience:\n• 2013-2016: Process engineer at SAIP Soluciones Integrales in Veracruz, México, Department of Process. Projects on Design and analysis of process networks and piping. Appointed Group leader of specialty Process in 2013.\n• 2012-2013: Design engineer at AMT, S.A. DE C.V. in Veracruz, México, Department of Process. Projects on Analysis of auxiliary plant services.\n• 2008-2009: Member of Evaluation Committee at CACEI, A.C. México, City. Projects on Evaluation processes for accreditation purposes of Engineering careers.\n• 2005–2007: Ph. D. student and Research Assistant at Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana – Iztapalapa.\n\nPublications:\nGonzález Cervantes, P.; Carmona Domínguez, J.R.; Pérez, Correa, S.; Miranda Medina, A. (2023) Simulación dinámica de un reactor HTL para la producción de biopetróleo crudo a partir de microalgas. Congreso Internacional de Investigación Academia Journals, Chetumal 2023, Tomo 7, 114.\nArticle/Conference paper\n\nLeo-Avelino, G.; Urrea-Garcia, G.R.; , Gómez-Rodríguez, J.; Pérez Correa, S.; Aguilar-Uscanga, M.G.  (2021) Natural Mexican Clinoptilolite for ethanol dehydration: adsorption-regeneration experimental parameter determination and scaling-up at Pilot Plant. Revista Mexicana de Ingeniería Química, Vol. 20, No. 3, Pro2358.\nAcademic article\n\nRojas-González, A. Miranda-Medina, A., Pérez Correa, S., Rodríguez Jímenez, del Carmen Rodríguez Jiménez (2018). Diseño de un alimento funcional a partir de mermas comerciales de Papaya (Carica papaya) y de Amaranto (Amaranthus hypochondriacus) para infantes y niños en comunidades rurales del estado de Veracruz. Congreso Internacional de Investigación Academia Journals, Celaya 2018, Tomo 28, 4749.\nArticle/Conference paper\n\nPérez-Correa, S.; González, P.; Alvarez, J. (2008). On-Line Optimizing Control for a Class of Batch Reactive Distillations Columns. Proceedings of the 17th IFAC World Congress (Seoul, Korea), 3263.\nArticle/Conference paper\n\nS. de Buruaga, I.; López, T.; Pérez, S.; Alvarez, J (2004). Calorimetric Estimation of Viscosity and Acid Number in Alkyd Reactors. Proceedings of the International Symposium on Advanced Control of Chemical Processes, ADCHEM (Hong Kong, China), 675.\nArticle/Conference paper\n\nPérez Correa, S.; Lapidus, G.T. (2000). Cinética de la Cianuración de Metales Preciosos en un Mineral. X Congreso Internacional de Metalurgia Extractiva, Mexico, City.\nArticle/Conference paper\n\n\nAdditional Professional Activities\n• Member (2023) of International Association of Engineers (IAENG).\n• Visitor professor of the Academic Board of Science and Engineering of Bioactive Compounds CACIB and the Multidisciplinary Research Program in Environment-Energy PMIAE – TECNM-Campus Veracruz.\n• Participation in direction and review of Research projects in the Biochemical Engineering, Professional resi