(96, 'Pablo González Cervantes', 'Pablo González C. is professor of Chemical Engineering and Biochemical Engineering programs at TecNM-Campus Veracruz. He has also been associate professor at Universidad Autonoma Metropolitana, and at Medicine School of Universidad Veracruzana.\nHis professional interests include process control, chemical reactors, and mathematical methods applied to chemical processes.', 'Ph. D. in Chemical Engineering, Universidad Autonoma Metropolitana, 2008.\nDoctoral dissertation: Control of solution homopolymer reactors.\n\nM. Sc. in Chemical Engineering, Universidad Autonoma Metropolitana, 2000.\nThesis: Estimation of solution homopolymer reactors.\n\nB. Sc. in Biochemical Engineering, Instituto Tecnologico de Veracruz, 1997.', 'Chemical process control\nChemical reactors engineering\nBioreactors engineering\nMass-transfer unit operations\nFluid mechanics\nHeat and mass transfer\nMathematical methods in process engineering\nThermodynamics', 'pablo.gc@veracruz.tecnm.mx', 'pabloGonzalezCervantes.webp', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4, 1, NULL, '2023-10-02', NULL, '2023-10-02'),
